  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good dance club songs?",
  "response": "Here are some popular dance club songs that have been known to get people moving on the dance floor:\n\n1. **\"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" by Justin Timberlake** - This upbeat track is perfect for getting everyone in a good mood and dancing.\n2. **\"Uptown Funk\" by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars** - A funky hit that's almost guaranteed to fill the dance floor.\n3. **\"Don't Stop the Music\" by Rihanna** - A club staple that keeps the energy high.\n4. **\"I Gotta Feeling\" by Black Eyed Peas** - An anthem that's perfect for late-night club vibes.\n5. **\"Levels\" by Avicii** - A classic EDM track that's great for dancing.\n6. **\"Yeah!\" by Usher ft. Lil Jon, Ludacris** - A timeless club hit that never fails to get people moving.\n7. **\"Higher Ground\" by TNGHT** - Great for those who love bass-heavy tracks.\n8. **\"Firework\" by Katy Perry** - An uplifting song that can inspire some energetic dance moves.\n9. **\"Get Lucky\" by Daft Punk ft. Pharrell Williams, Nile Rodgers** - A groovy track that's perfect for dancing.\n10. **\"Feel So Close\" by Calvin Harris** - An electronic dance hit that's sure to keep the party going.\n\nThese songs span various genres and eras, but they all have one thing in common: they're great for dancing in a club setting!",
